{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d444c7f-b612-4ab1-8006-f3cc4ba7fdc9","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` v3 NuGet package (replaces framework + adapter + analyzers in one package)\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\nYour test code is already compatible — MSTest v3 uses the same namespace and attributes.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01BwJKb39gwR6pbywhtDDdXr","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NPY1MzqPb9bVzj6hCeXF6m","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5376473c954f4208b5a10dae2daa306c/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5376473c954f4208b5a10dae2daa306c/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"b114a2e1-af46-47a2-acef-8e2ff974b43a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET Framework test project targeting net462 that uses an old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`. They want to upgrade to MSTest v3.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the old assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** - MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package (replacing the old `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` combo)\n\n\n3. **Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** to a current version and verify the target framework is compatible - MSTest v3 supports net462 and newer\n4. The namespace stays the same since MSTest v3 still uses `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting`, so the `using` statements don't need to change\n\nFor the migration, I can either use the single `MSTest` meta-package (v3.x) which bundles everything together, or go with individual packages like `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`. The main steps are removing the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`, swapping in the new NuGet packages, and updating the test SDK - the actual test code should work as-is since MSTest v3 maintains backward compatibility with the existing attributes.","outputTokens":911,"requestId":"0410:341029:179BDD4:190344B:6A033768"},"id":"efeec91b-9387-411d-95fc-971f03d2bb50","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:44.608Z","parentId":"a682a875-5135-4334-91ac-661c8bb06430"}
